{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"2332","heading":"Priorities; uniformity; preferences; impairment of rights","label":"2332 Priorities; uniformity; preferences; impairment of rights","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch24/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Transfer of FunctionsAtomic Energy Commission abolished and functions transferred by sections 5814 and 5841 of this title. See also Transfer of Functions notes set out under those sections."],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"be uniform in each class or subclass of property;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The retention and recruitment of personnel essential to the atomic energy program;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The minimization of dislocations within the community;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The expeditious accomplishment of the disposal program; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fb%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The desirability of encouraging private firms to locate or remain in the community;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":null,"label":"c","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"give the occupant of a Government-owned single family house, and the senior occupant of a duplex house, at least ninety days in which to exercise the first right of priority;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":null,"label":"d","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"permit persons who have formerly been occupants, project-connected persons, or inhabitants of the community, upon application therefor, to have such priority as the Commission finds to be fair and equitable; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":null,"label":"e","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2332","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs2332%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not impair any rights, including purchase rights, conferred by existing leases and covenants.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
